What 's the background ? Giuliani appeared Wednesday on Fox News ' " Hannity , " where he attempted to explain that no campaign finance laws were violated in attorney Michael Cohen 's payment to Clifford . " I was talking about the $ 130,000 payment , the settlement payment , which is a very regular thing for lawyers to do , " Giulani told host Sean Hannity . " The question there was , the only possible violation there would be , was it a campaign finance violation ? Which usually would result in a fine by the way , not this big stormtroopers coming in and breaking down his apartment and breaking down his office . " Giuliani added , " That was money that was paid by his lawyer , the way that I would do , out of his law firm funds , or whatever funds , does n’t matter …
